    %h5 Images
    %p
      To embed an image, use markdown syntax with the image ID:
    %pre
      ![](42 "12,10,8,6,c")
    %p
      %strong Image ID:
      The number in parentheses is the image ID (found on the <a href="/images">Images</a> page).
    %p
      %strong Alt Text:
      The text in square brackets is for assistive technologies. If left blank, the image's caption will be used automatically.
    %p
      %strong Breakpoints:
      The quoted text controls responsive sizing across different screen sizes. Use 1-6 comma-separated integers (between 1-12) for Bootstrap column widths at breakpoints xs, sm, md, lg, xl, xx.
    %ul
      %li
        %code "12,10,8,6"
        → Full width on mobile (xs=12), narrower on larger screens (sm=10, md=8, lg=6)
      %li
        %code "12,10"
        → Two breakpoints only (xs=12, sm=10)
      %li
        %code ""
        or omit quotes → Default full width (xs=12)
    %p
      %strong Caption Display:
      Optionally append
      %code c
      or
      %code C
      to show the image caption:
    %ul
      %li
        %code "c"
        or
        %code "12,10,8,c"
        → Caption displayed, centered
      %li
        %code "C"
        or
        %code "12,10,8,C"
        → Caption displayed, left-aligned
      %li No flag → Caption not displayed (default)
    %p
      %strong Examples:
    %pre
      ![](42)                 # Full width, no caption
      ![](42 "c")             # Full width, centered caption
      ![](42 "12,10,8,6,C")   # Responsive sizing, left-aligned caption
      ![My description](42)   # Custom alt text, no caption
    %h5 YouTube Videos
    %p
      To embed a YouTube video, use the same markdown syntax with the 11-character video ID:
    %pre
      ![](dQw4w9WgXcQ "12,10,8,6,c")
    %p
      %strong Video ID:
      The 11-character ID in parentheses is from the YouTube URL. For example:
    %ul
      %li
        %code https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQw4w9WgXcQ
        → ID is
        %code dQw4w9WgXcQ
      %li
        %code https://youtu.be/dQw4w9WgXcQ
        → ID is
        %code dQw4w9WgXcQ
    %p
      %strong Caption:
      The text in square brackets becomes the video caption (only shown if you include the
      %code c
      or
      %code C
      flag).
    %p
      %strong Breakpoints:
      Same as images - use 1-6 comma-separated integers (1-12) for responsive sizing. Videos maintain 16:9 aspect ratio automatically.
    %p
      %strong Caption Display:
      Same as images - append
      %code c
      (centered) or
      %code C
      (left-aligned) to show the caption.
    %p
      %strong Examples:
    %pre
      ![My video](dQw4w9WgXcQ)          # Full width, no caption
      ![My video](dQw4w9WgXcQ "c")      # Full width, centered caption
      ![My video](dQw4w9WgXcQ "8,6")    # Responsive sizing, no caption
      ![My video](dQw4w9WgXcQ "8,6,C")  # Responsive sizing, left-aligned caption
